Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi said schools planning any water-related activities in Gauteng - will now have to get approval from the provincial education department. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng education MEC Panyaza Lesufi is set to release the forensic report into the death of Enock Mpianzi on Wednesday. The Mpianzi family lawyer, Ian Levitt, has confirmed to eNCA that the family will only be receiving a copy of the report later on Wednesday morning. READ: Release of report into Mpianzi drowning delayed The report was meant to be released two weeks ago, but the family asked that it be delayed as their input had not been included in the report. The Parktown Boys' High School pupil drowned during a Grade 8 orientation camp in January. It's believed no life jackets were provided. READ: Lesufi to release forensic report into Enock Mpianzi's death The report was meant to be released two weeks ago. The school headmaster was soon suspended after the incident.